Package gw.api.policy.refresh.relink

package gw.api.policy.refresh.relink
  • Related Packages

    Description

  • Class
    Description
    BaseLinkHandler<T extends KeyableBean>
    Base implementation of LinkHandler that implements most of the required behavior, leaving the handling of the case where there is no match (in either case) in the new policy to subclass implementations.
    ClaimLinkPreservingFilter
    A RelinkFilter for preserving specified "broken links" in the case where the target of the link has been removed (i.e., not present in the new Policy).
    DefaultLinkHandler<T extends KeyableBean>
    The default behavior is to: Relink if there is a match for the entity from the existing Policy in the new Policy. If there is no match, behavior depends on link direction.
    DefaultRelinkHandler<T extends KeyableBean>
    The default RelinkHandler, which is used in the absence of any configured handler for a given entity.
    Direction
    Indicates the direction of the relinking.
    IgnoreIfNotMatchedLinkHandler<T extends KeyableBean>
    Simply ignores a removed target (If matched, default behavior is followed).
    LinkHandler<T extends KeyableBean>
    Interface that specifies foreign key-level relinking.
    PerLinkHandler<T extends KeyableBean>
    Base class for RelinkHandler implementations that only want to override default behavior for specific links.
    PerLinkHandler.Builder<E extends KeyableBean>
    Builder for creating a PerLinkHandler.
    RelinkBean<T extends KeyableBean>
    Represents a bean in the existing Claim/Policy that needs to be relinked when the existing Policy is replaced.
    RelinkBeanImpl<T extends KeyableBean>
    Represents a bean in the existing Claim/Policy that needs to be relinked when the existing Policy is replaced.
    RelinkContext
    Context for the Policy Refresh relinking step.
    RelinkFilter
    Interface for pre- and/or post-processing the Claim/Policy during the step where the Claim is relinked to the new Policy.
    RelinkHandler<T extends KeyableBean>
    Interface that specifies entity-level handling of relinking.
    RelinkItem<T extends KeyableBean>
    Represents a single link (or array) that needs to be relinked.
